 S_n=\frac1{1+a}+\frac1{2(1+2a)}+\frac1{3(1+3a)}+\cdots
 a=\frac12,\frac13,\frac14,\ldots 
\frac1{n(1+na)}=\frac1n-\frac a{1+na}
\,a=\frac12\;
\sum_{n=1}^k\left(\frac1n-\frac1{n+2}\right)=1-\frac13+\frac12-\frac14+\frac13-\frac15+\frac14-\frac16+\ldots\xrightarrow[k\to\infty]{}\frac32
S_n=\sum_{i=1}^{n}\frac{1}{i(1+ia)}
\frac{1}{i(1+ia)}=\frac{1}{i}-\frac{1}{\frac{1}{a}+i}
 \lim_{n \rightarrow \infty}S_n=\sum_{i=1}^{\infty}\frac{1}{i(1+ia)} =\sum_{i=1}^{\infty}(\frac{1}{i}-\frac{1}{\frac{1}{a}+i}) =\sum_{i=1}^{\frac{1}{a}}{\frac{1}{i}}
